cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the segmentation of brain MRI images using active contour models, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach using globally convex methods, which is related to optimization and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The use of energy functionals and dual minimization also suggests a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
